---
import FootnoteRef from '../FootnoteRef.astro';
import type { FootnoteRegistry } from '../../lib/footnote-registry';

export interface Props {
  registry: FootnoteRegistry;
}

const { registry } = Astro.props;
---

<article>
  <h1>Getting Started with Astro</h1>
  
  <p>
    Astro is a modern web framework<FootnoteRef id="ABC_123" registry={registry} /> that allows you to build fast, content-focused websites. Unlike traditional frameworks, Astro ships zero JavaScript by default, making your sites incredibly fast.
  </p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  
  <p>
    One of Astro's most powerful features is its component islands architecture<FootnoteRef id="DEF_456" registry={registry} />. This allows you to use components from different frameworks like React, Vue, or Svelte within the same project.
  </p>

  <p>
    The framework also supports excellent developer experience with features like:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Hot module replacement</li>
    <li>TypeScript support out of the box</li>
    <li>Built-in optimizations</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    For more technical implementation details<FootnoteRef id="GHI_789" registry={registry} />, check the official documentation.
  </p>
</article>